### Akeeba Panopticon API — Sites (read-only)
###
### PhpStorm HTTP Client request file. Use the run gutter icon next to each block
### or right-click → Run All Requests in File.
###
### Replace the env vars below or define them in a sibling `http-client.env.json`.

@hostname = https://panopticon.local
@token    = REPLACE-ME-WITH-A-REAL-TOKEN

### List sites (recommended: Bearer auth)
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/sites
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### List sites with filters and pagination
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/sites?search=example&cmsType=joomla&limit=10&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Get a single site by id
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### --- Alternative authentication surfaces -------------------------------------

### Custom header (X-Panopticon-Token)
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/sites
X-Panopticon-Token: {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### GET parameter — NOT recommended for production.
# WARNING: query-string tokens are leaked through web-server access logs and the
# Referer header. Documented as a footgun in assets/api/docs/overview.md.
# Use Bearer auth in real automations.
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/sites?_panopticon_token={{token}}
Accept: application/json

### --- Write endpoints -------------------------------------------------------

### Add a new site
PUT {{hostname}}/api/v1/site
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name":    "Example",
  "url":     "https://example.com/api",
  "enabled": true,
  "notes":   "Production site",
  "groups":  [1, 2],
  "config":  {
    "config": {
      "cmsType":     "joomla",
      "apiKey":      "REPLACE-WITH-THE-CONNECTOR-TOKEN"
    }
  }
}

### Modify an existing site (only the fields you send are updated)
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name":    "Example (renamed)",
  "enabled": false,
  "config":  {
    "config.domain.warning": 180
  }
}

### Refresh site information synchronously
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/refresh
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Fix a stuck Joomla core update site (Joomla sites only)
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/fixjoomlacoreupdate
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### --- CMS update lifecycle -------------------------------------------------

### Schedule a CMS update (Joomla or WordPress); set "force": true to override version-skip
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/cmsupdate
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{ "force": false }

### Cancel a not-yet-running CMS update
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/cmsupdate/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Clear a failed CMS update task
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/cmsupdate/clear
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### --- Extensions ----------------------------------------------------------

### List extensions
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/extensions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Refresh extensions info (synchronous, may take seconds)
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/extensions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Clear a failed extensions-update task
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/extensions/clear
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Reset (optionally purge the queue too)
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/extensions/reset
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{ "resetqueue": true }

### Schedule a single extension for update
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/extensions/scheduleupdate/42
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Cancel a single extension's queued update
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/extensions/cancel/42
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Get an extension's download key (Joomla only)
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/extension/42/downloadkey
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Set an extension's download key (Joomla only)
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1/extension/42/downloadkey
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{ "key": "ABC-123-XYZ" }
